mber":1,"category":"family","header":"Named Hooker; mother Julia died when she was","body":"Sarah Hooker Hopkins was born November 17, 1837, her middle name Hooker honoring her mother Julia Ann Hooker's family line. Her mother died in Chicago in September 1842 when Sarah was just four years old, leaving her father Frederick Hopkins to raise her."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Settled Monte Vista, Colorado","body":"Sarah Hooker Hopkins and Josiah Perkins Woodbury settled at Monte Vista in Rio Grande County, Colorado — far from Rutland, Vermont, where she was born. Two of their six children died very young: Annie Lawrence at four months, Jean Hopkins at four years."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Husband was treasurer of the Panama Railroad","body":"Sarah Hooker Hopkins married Joseph Perkins Woodbury — a Vermont lawyer who had served as treasurer of the Panama Railroad on the Isthmus — in Rutland on November 19, 1861. They moved to Monte Vista, Colorado, then eventually to Los Angeles, where Sarah died January 23, 1915, and where Joseph was buried after his death in 1895."}],"naming_inspiration":[],"quotes":[],"documents":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM411","plot_notes":"Forest Lawn Memorial Park, Glendale, Los Angeles County CA. FGA #235629853."},"residence":{"country":"United States"},"sources":[{"short":"EH 1909 #2773"}],"research_sources":[],"slug":"sarah-hopkins-1837"},"H01420":{"id":"H01420","is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"former_ids":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Julia Ann Hooker","first_name":"Julia","middle_name":"Ann","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":["Hopkins"]},"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1810,"month":9,"day":9,"city":"Rutland","county":"Rutland","state":"Vermont","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1842,"month":9,"day":27,"city":"Chicago","county":"Cook","state":"Illinois","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is